HEADWORD: Tenderling
<hw>Ten"der*ling</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One
made tender by too much kindness; a fondling.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
<rj><au>W. Harrison (1586).</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>One of the first antlers of a
deer.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tenderloin</ent>⟦br⟧
